WILD VAMPIRE

Wild Vampires are the most powerful vampire type available to players.  Unlike
Secondary Vampires, Wild Vampires have been transformed by a Vampire
Intelligence directly, granting them vastly superior attributes and MDC.
They are ancient predators, cunning and terrifying.  Few factions on Rifts
Earth are willing to engage a Wild Vampire in direct combat.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 9-24   ME: 7-22   MA: 8-28   PS: 16-36 (Supernatural)
  PP: 9-24   PE: 14-34  PB: 8-28   Spd: 12-32

DAMAGE POOL:
  MDC: 4d6 x10 + 60 (approx 100-300 MDC)
  HP: PE + 2d6

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - MDC body: immune to SDC/HP weapons (very high MDC pool)
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance (exceptional values)
  - Rapid regeneration
  - Hypnotic gaze
  - Immunity to normal weapons

PENALTIES:
  - Not OCC eligible
  - Sunlight: 2d6 MDC per melee round
  - Wild fire: double MDC damage
  - Cannot enter dwelling without invitation
  - Stake through the heart: instant death

OCC ELIGIBLE: No.
ALIGNMENT: Most Wild Vampires are Miscreant or Diabolic.

See also: secondary vampire, werewolf, races
